<div id="review_72300311" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/72300311" />
    <a title="reading is my hustle" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2069203-reading-is-my-hustle"><img alt="reading is my hustle" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1482541792p2/2069203.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/72300311?book_show_action=true">Sep 23, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="reading is my hustle" class="user" itemprop="url" name="reading is my hustle" href="/user/show/2069203-reading-is-my-hustle">reading is my hustle</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2069203-reading-is-my-hustle?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2069203-reading-is-my-hustle?shelf=culture-or-setting-israel">culture-or-setting-israel</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2069203-reading-is-my-hustle?shelf=fiction-ww-ii">fiction-ww-ii</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer72300311" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5894136978921930195">This novel (based on a true event) about four wounded and damaged Jewish women in the internment camp of Atlit has a gripping storyline but was disappointing overall. Of the four women, I was only able to keep two of them straight. The others I had to keep checking the book flap to identify their character. This is not to say that their back stories were not compelling. Mostly, I just wanted more information overall about each character.<br/><br/>In terms of her writing craft, Anita Diamant continues to d</span>
  <span id="freeText5894136978921930195" style="display:none">This novel (based on a true event) about four wounded and damaged Jewish women in the internment camp of Atlit has a gripping storyline but was disappointing overall. Of the four women, I was only able to keep two of them straight. The others I had to keep checking the book flap to identify their character. This is not to say that their back stories were not compelling. Mostly, I just wanted more information overall about each character.<br /><br />In terms of her writing craft, Anita Diamant continues to dazzle. I liked that the pace of camp life was reflected in the telling of the story and that threaded throughout the novel was the question "why did I survive, while others did not?"<br /><br />It's a damn good question. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="5894136978921930195" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
